# Architecture

- Client `feature-*` modules must not depend on each other; compose them only from `app/shared`.
- `core`, `core-network`, `core-database`, `core-ui`, and `core-platform` are shared building blocks.
- Backend exposes HTTP under `/api/...` and WebSocket `/ws/game` for game sync.
- WebSocket payloads should use kotlinx.serialization-friendly DTOs on the client; keep server validation authoritative.
- `expect/actual` in `core-platform` must provide Android, iOS, and desktop actuals when adding new declarations.
